Deal with larger data set:¶

  1. 384 well plates
  2. 6 X 48hrs movie per well
  3. "Hopefully" 1 image every 20min
  4. 3 colors
  5. sCMOS camera with ~ 6Mb per image
  6. ~1M images (~6TB)

def show_frame(path, row = 'A', column = '01',image = 'image1', log=True):
    with h5py.File(path, 'r') as f:
        img = f[row+column][image][()]
        hist = np.histogram(img, bins=np.arange(0, img.max()))
        fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize=(24,12))
        axes[0].imshow(img, cmap="gray",interpolation='nearest')
        axes[0].axis("off")
        axes[0].autoscale_view('tight')
        if log:
            axes[1].semilogy(hist[1][:-1], hist[0], lw=2)
        else:
            axes[1].plot(hist[1][:-1], hist[0], lw=2)
        axes[1].set_title('Histogram', fontsize=25)
        axes[1].set_xlabel('Pixel value', fontsize=15)
        axes[1].set_ylabel('Frequency', fontsize=15)

labeled_coins = label(segmentation)
